  "lifecycle_summary": "NewServer accepts an http.Handler (the query mux) and calls ReadOnlyTools() to populate s.tools. In HTTP mode RunHTTP calls httpMux to compose admin routes with MCP-specific routes (GET /sse, POST /mcp/message, GET /health) and mounts the query handler under /api/. In stdio mode Run reads newline-delimited JSON-RPC from stdin and writes responses to stdout. Both modes call handleMessage for each request. For tools/call, handleMessage calls dispatchTool which resolves a route via resolveRoute, builds an http.Request, and calls handler.ServeHTTP through an httptest.ResponseRecorder. The response body is checked with parseCanonicalEnvelope; if it matches the PCG envelope shape it is returned as a two-block mcpToolResult (text summary + embedded resource); otherwise it is returned as a single text block.",
